  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Importing the required libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Loading required package: ggplot2\n",
      "Loading required package: sp\n",
      "Checking rgeos availability: FALSE\n",
      " \tNote: when rgeos is not available, polygon geometry \tcomputations in maptools depend on gpclib,\n",
      " \twhich has a restricted licence. It is disabled by default;\n",
      " \tto enable gpclib, type gpclibPermit()\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "library(\"ggmap\") \n",
    "library(\"maptools\") \n",
    "library(maps)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Taking the input location as a string"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "inputLocation <- \"Buffalo\"\n",
    "inputLat <- 42.88645\n",
    "inputLon <- -78.87837"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Getting the geocode and storing it in the locations data frame"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 65,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Information from URL : http://www.datasciencetoolkit.org/maps/api/geocode/json?address=Buffalo&sensor=false\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "if(inputLocation!=\"\")\n",
    "    {\n",
    "    locations <- geocode(inputLocation, source =\"dsk\") \n",
    "    inputLat <- as.numeric(locations[[2]])\n",
    "    inputLon <- as.numeric(locations[[1]])\n",
    "    }"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Getting the details of WOEID from the closestTrendLocations function by passing the obtained lat, lon as parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 66,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "woeid = closestTrendLocations(inputLat,inputLon)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Displaying the woeid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 67,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<table>\n",
       "<thead><tr><th scope=col>name</th><th scope=col>country</th><th scope=col>woeid</th></tr></thead>\n",
       "<tbody>\n",
       "\t<tr><td>Toronto</td><td>Canada </td><td>4118   </td></tr>\n",
       "</tbody>\n",
       "</table>\n"
      ],
      "text/latex": [
       "\\begin{tabular}{r|lll}\n",
       " name & country & woeid\\\\\n",
       "\\hline\n",
       "\t Toronto & Canada  & 4118   \\\\\n",
       "\\end{tabular}\n"
      ],
      "text/markdown": [
       "\n",
       "name | country | woeid | \n",
       "|---|\n",
       "| Toronto | Canada  | 4118    | \n",
       "\n",
       "\n"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "  name    country woeid\n",
       "1 Toronto Canada  4118 "
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "woeid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Getting the trends of the location from woeid"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trends = getTrends(woeid$woeid)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Storing the top 10 trends in a trends2 variable"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trends2 <- trends[1:10,]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Printing the top 10 trending topics for input location"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Trending topics for buffalo are #NBACelebGame #CanM20 #BlueJackets Kyrie Irving Russell Westbrook #FamilyDayWeekend Logan Masjid Toronto #MakeASongWhiny Tigres"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cat(\"Trending topics for\",inputLocation,\"are\", trends2$name)"
   ]
  }
